CHELICERAE. Small, flat tooth on retrolateral surface of basal segment, opposite to
                  bifid tooth; retrolateral surface of claw with row of setae restricted to base;
                  claw with five teeth; row of eleven setae on prolateral surface of basal segment;
                  bifid tooth on basal segment with dorsal cusp larger than ventral cusp.
